name: MedicationDrugClass
title: Medication Drug Class
publisher: HL7 US Realm Program Management Steward
description:
Per HITSP (and C-CDA): This identifies the pharmacological drug class, such as Cephalosporins. Shall contain a value descending from the NDF-RT concept types of “Mechanism of Action - N0000000223”, “Physiologic Effect - N0000009802” or “Chemical Structure - N0000000002”`. NUI will be used as the concept code.

Unclear if this should be limited to medications or should also be used for environmental, food, etc.
purpose: (Clinical Focus: Pharmacologic classification concepts that can be used to group substances. Primarily used for allergen and intolerance substance classes.),(Data Element Scope: Elements representing substances.),(Inclusion Criteria: Any concept that can represent a substance classification. Originally NDF-RT but in 2018 uses MED-RT),(Exclusion Criteria: concepts not described in the inclusion criteria)
